sequenceDiagram
    participant Be as platform backend<br/>(launchd / systemd-user)
    participant Tick as aos tick
    participant FS as runs/ + tick.log
    participant Backend as backend.State

    Be->>Tick: invoke at tick_interval
    Tick->>Tick: scan <aos_home>/agents/
    Tick->>FS: FileRunStore.Load(runs/)
    Tick->>Tick: DetectMissed (latest uncovered slot per agent)

    alt new misses found
        Tick->>FS: delete stale miss-*.json for agent
        Tick->>FS: write miss-<agent>-<expectedAt>.json
    else current slot already recorded
        Tick->>Tick: skip (idempotent)
    end

    Tick->>Tick: SweepStaleRunning (running > 1h → error)
    alt stale records found
        Tick->>FS: rewrite <id>.json with status=error,<br/>error="no completion record", exitCode=1
    end

    Tick->>Backend: backend.State(spec)
    Backend-->>Tick: managed | drift | empty | error(...)

    Tick->>FS: append "[tick] ..." to tick.log
    Tick-->>Be: exit 0 (stdout: log line or JSON outcome)

    Note over Be: Missed slots while asleep<br/>are re-fired natively by<br/>launchd / Persistent=true.<br/>aos does NOT dispatch them.
